<headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 14 at 12:45PM EDT  by NWS Blacksburg</headline>
<description>...Strong thunderstorms will impact portions of southwestern
Rockbridge, northern Bedford, central Botetourt and northwestern
Amherst Counties and the City of Buena Vista through 115 PM EDT...
At 1244 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from near Oronoco to Glasgow to near Natural Bridge
to near Glen Wilton. Movement was southeast at 60 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Buena Vista...
Buchanan...
Glasgow...
Big Island...
Eagle Rock...
Coleman Falls...
and Snowden.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN
MAX WIND GUST...50 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
